# Form field labels

## Click label → focus control

Every editable field label must activate its control when clicked.

- Prefer `FieldLabel` with `htmlFor` matching the control’s `id`.
- Or wrap the control in a native `<label>` (as in discipline selects).
- Do **not** use a bare `<span className="form-label">` next to an input
  without `htmlFor` / wrapping `<label>`.
- Keep `FieldHint` **outside** the `<label>` (FieldLabel already does this) so
  the (i) click opens the tip instead of focusing the field.

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
<FieldLabel htmlFor="profile-nickname" hint={t.profileNicknameHint}>
  {t.profileNicknameLabel}
</FieldLabel>
<input id="profile-nickname" className="form-control" ... />

// ❌ BAD — label click does nothing
<span className="form-label">{t.profileNicknameLabel}</span>
<input className="form-control" ... />
```

Readonly summary rows may omit `htmlFor` (no focus target).

## Field hints (i)

- `FieldHint` trigger uses `tabIndex={-1}` — not in sequential Tab order.
- Do not add `tabIndex={0}` (or omit `-1`) on `.hint-trigger`.
- Hints open via pointer (click / hover); Esc still closes when open.
